See all available databases
\l
\list

Create a new database
CREATE DATABASE college;

Connect to / Continue with an existing database
\c college

Show all tables inside current database
\dt

Describe structure of a table
\d student

See which database you’re currently connected to
SELECT current_database();

View all data from a table
SELECT * FROM student;

Delete / Drop a database
DROP DATABASE college;
	
Create database only if it doesn’t exist
CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS college;

Drop database only if it exists
DROP DATABASE IF EXISTS college;

Quit PostgreSQL
\q
